Thằng Ngọc Quỳnh is a Junior AI Engineer with 0 years of commercial experience, specializing in Natural Language Processing and Machine Learning. Their core expertise lies in architectures such as Microservices and models like TinyBERT, utilizing frameworks like LangChain and Streamlit to design and implement multi-stage pipelines and sentiment analysis systems. With a strong academic background, they have worked on various projects, including a multi-stage RAG agent with FlowiseAI, achieving notable results in sentiment classification with 87% accuracy using TinyBERT and Logistic Regression. Their experience also encompasses designing and implementing database systems, such as a dental clinic management system using MySQL and MongoDB with a microservices model.

Technically, Thằng Ngọc Quỳnh is proficient in programming languages like Python and SQL, and has hands-on experience with databases including MySQL and MongoDB. They are also familiar with devops and cloud tools, although their current expertise is more focused on tools and platforms such as FlowiseAI, Odoo, Git, GitHub, MS Office, and Jira. Their domain knowledge spans Service-Oriented Architecture, Enterprise Resource Planning, and software development methodologies like SDLC, Waterfall, Agile, and Scrum. With a solid foundation in computer networks and data communications from Tôn Đức Thắng University, they are well-versed in concepts like APIs, ERD, and RAG, demonstrating a strong potential for growth in the AI engineering field, particularly in areas requiring expertise in NLP, machine learning, and software development.